Generic single-database configuration using an async SQLAlchemy
engine (asyncpg). The database URL is loaded from application settings
(`app.core.config.get_settings().database_url`) inside `env.py` rather
than from `alembic.ini`, so it is always sourced from the environment
/ `.env` file, consistent with the rest of the project.

Common commands:

    alembic revision -m "description"   # create a new empty migration
    alembic upgrade head                # apply all migrations
    alembic downgrade -1                 # roll back one migration